Revista Factum was under prolonged cyber attacks for denouncing corruption, the government of El Salvador had banned it. The alleged perpetrator of the attacks has been identified as a computer engineer acting, from the University of Oriente, El Salvador. The intense cyber attacks in October last year, cost the news site almost a week's downtime. On 13 October, the Denial of Service attacks started, and on the third day, when the magazine's website went offline, a businessman placed a paid advertisement in the press claiming to have bribed the news outlets' editor. Qurium's forensics investigation attributes the attacks and places the attacker at the Universidad de Oriente. The university collaborated by identifying the person and the machine from which the attacks were carried out. Qurium's forensics report: DDoS attacks against Salvadoran "Factum Magazine" in El Salvador attributed to University infrastructure.